It seems the `availableModels` prop in `ModelSelectionDialog.tsx` is changing between renders, causing the filtering inconsistencies. I'll investigate `App.tsx`, its likely parent, to see how `availableModels` is managed and why it's so unstable.

To fix this, I'll cache all available models in a new `allAvailableModels` state variable within `App.tsx`. I'll populate this state once on component mount using `useEffect`. Then, I'll modify `handleModelSelectionOpen` to use the cached `allAvailableModels` and pass it to `ModelSelectionDialog`. This will ensure a consistent model list. I'll use the `replace` tool to carefully update `App.tsx`, rereading the file first to ensure I have the latest version.
